What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Smart Grid Networking Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Smart Grid Networking Market

Surge in the rate of digitization especially in the developing economies, growing adoption of property management software solutions by small and medium scale enterprises and increased investment and deployment of smart grid technologies such as smart meters are the major factors attributable to the growth of the smart grid networking market. Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the smart grid networking market will exhibit a CAGR of 11.40% for the forecast period of 2022-2029.

Smart grid networking refers to a system of electronic network that enables two-way digital communication system and real-time collection pertaining to electricity demand, supply and other relevant data. Smart grid networking involves the application of smart sensors and power meters during the distribution and transmission process of electricity.

Rising demand from the buildings and construction industry especially in the developing economies will emerge as the major market growth driving factor. Surging demand for cost efficient energy globally, growing adoption of new and advanced technology, growing introducing software-based architecture in emerging nations, surging investment in the workforce management and quality monitoring and strengthening IT industry in developing economies such as India and China will further aggravate the growth of the market. Rising construction of residential and commercial properties, growth in the proliferation of distributed energy sources such as photovoltaic (PV) , rising availability of high speed internet facility, supportive regulatory framework of governments and growth in the number of research and development proficiencies by the major players are some other factors bolstering the growth of the market.

However, lack of technological expertise in underdeveloped and developing economies high installation costs of smart grids will act as growth restraints for the market. Also, dearth of awareness in the underdeveloped economies and complexities associated with the storage and management of data generated by smart grid infrastructure will yet again hamper the market growth rate. Lack of strong infrastructural facilities in the backward economies and lack of standardisation and data management efficiency will also challenge the market growth rate.

